title: Slim Harpo - The Best of Slim Harpo (1989) [FLAC]
description:
another great, but almost forgotten bluesman - Slim Harpo aka James Moore (1924 - 1070) from Louisiana

As his name indicates, he played the harp, but he was also a really great songwriter. His songs like I'm a King Bee or Shake Your Hips were covered by Muddy Waters, the Rolling Stones, the Pretty Things, the Yardbirds, the Kinks, Them, the Grateful Dead and the Doors. And Shake Your Hips was the inspiration for ZZ Top's La Grange.
